Speaking on a smuggled-in phone, the young man said he was enduring a "living hell". He told AFP news agency of overcrowding, disease and suicides at the facility in the southern province of Jizan. It was the latest in a series of disturbing reports on conditions being experienced by large numbers of Ethiopian migrants who are being held in Saudi Arabia. The Ethiopian government says it hasn't had sufficient coronavirus quarantine facilities to bring home its stranded citizens more quickly. --BBC--